    <h1>Gutter Cleaning in Vancouver — Protect Your Home from Rain, Moss, and Water Damage</h1>

    <p>Vancouver’s heavy rainfall, dense tree cover, and damp coastal climate make clogged gutters one of the most common causes of property damage. Leaves, pine needles, moss, and roof debris quickly block drainage systems, preventing water from flowing safely away from the home. When gutters overflow, moisture can penetrate siding, roofing, and foundations — leading to leaks, mold growth, structural deterioration, and costly repairs.</p>

    <p>Clean Gutters Crew (CGC) provides professional gutter cleaning services across Vancouver to keep homes safe, dry, and well-maintained in every season. Our team understands the unique challenges of local properties — from heritage houses surrounded by mature trees to modern homes exposed to Pacific storms.</p>

    <p>We serve homeowners throughout the city, including West Point Grey, Kitsilano, Dunbar, Kerrisdale, Marpole, Oakridge, Mount Pleasant, Hastings-Sunrise, Renfrew-Collingwood, Fraserview, and Downtown residential areas. No matter where your home is located, we tailor our service to the specific conditions of your neighbourhood.</p>

    <h2>Why Regular Gutter Cleaning Is Essential in Vancouver</h2>

    <p>Blocked gutters can cause serious long-term problems for homes in the Lower Mainland. Overflowing water may run behind siding, damage fascia boards, weaken roof edges, erode soil around the foundation, or seep into basements. Constant moisture also accelerates mold growth, paint failure, and deterioration of exterior materials.</p>

    <p>Routine professional maintenance is one of the most effective ways to protect your property, avoid expensive repairs, and preserve your home’s value.</p>

    <h2>Our Professional Cleaning Process</h2>

    <p>Clean Gutters Crew uses safe equipment and proven techniques designed for residential properties in Metro Vancouver. We remove debris by hand or vacuum, clear all blockages, flush downspouts, and ensure proper water flow through the entire system.</p>

    <p>Our technicians also check for loose sections, minor damage, or drainage issues that could lead to future problems. We work carefully to protect roofing materials, landscaping, and outdoor surfaces, leaving your property clean and tidy after the job is complete.</p>

